node.text:
To crown champions, a set criteria is required. ✔️
Read more on how surfing is judged ahead of its debut in Japan, link in bio.
#tokyo2020 #surf

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SURF JUDGING EXPLAINED JUDGING OVERVIEW Judges evaluate the conditions and set a judging criteria for the day. Scoring is dependent on the maneuvers performed on a wave based on the criteria. ONLSURF EST1976 @WSL'.

Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'CONDITIONS Surf conditions change based on swell, winds, and tides. "Judging Criteria" is set each day to establish a guide of how the day's competition will be scored based on the surf conditions. MANEUVERS Judges score competitors based on degree of difficulty, progression, and variety of maneuvers completed on a wave. Fundamental surf maneuvers include: @WSL'.
Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text.
Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎BARRELS ه When a surfer rides inside the curl or tube of a wave and exits without falling. @WSL‎'‎.
Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'AIRS M When a surfer rises above the top of a wave and lands back on their surfboard. @WSL'.

Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SCORING Based on the Judging Criteria, the judging panel applies a score from 0.0 10 for each wave surfed. •Scoring scale: 0.0 POOR 2.0-3.9 FAIR 4.0-5.9 AVERAGE 6.0-7.9 GOOD 8.0-10.0 EXCELLENT The winner of a heat is determined by the competitor' highest two scores added together (out of 20 points]. @WSL'.

Photo by World Surf League on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Judges analyze the following elements when scoring waves, depending on the day' conditions: Speed, power and flow Commitment and degree of difficulty Innovative and progressive maneuvers Combination of major maneuvers Variety of maneuvers @WSL'.
